The opposition has been urged to stop peddling propaganda against the Jubilee administration and instead focus on uniting Kenyans.Radio presenter Gathoni Wamuchomba, who has declared interest in Kiambu woman representative, said the opposition has focused on rubbishing the good work of the government. The Jubilee administration focuses on transforming the lives of Kenyans through development and offering better services. The opposition is using divisive politics by tarninshing the work of the government, she said.Wamuchomba spoke during a fundraiser at Our Lady of Fatima Catholic Church in Ndumberi village, Kiambu town, on Sunday. She said the country needs to be united and warned that propaganda politics is a recipe of chaos and hatred. The development record of the Jubilee administration speaks for itself, Wamuchomba said.